 </span><hr size=1> So I saw in the Elaa's last post thread that a dev said that SB's main advantage is being able to perf with 2h weapons, and thus do not deserve more spec points.  I was thinking about that, and to me it seemed silly so I conducted a green svart killing test.  I used two setups:<br>
<br>
Setup 1:  2h Infernal soulblade, 5.5 sp with stats 38+8 sword and 34+2 crit.<br>
<br>
Setup 2:  Arcanium sword 4.1 sp with infernal spined axe 4.0 sp with stats 38+2 sword, 39+11 L axe, and 34+2 cs.<br>
<br>
I went to spin and perfed 10 thralls with each setup and recorded the damage.  With setup 1 the damage is the perf style+the sword base damage.  With setup 2 the damage is the perf style + sword base+L. axe base.<br>
<br>
The averaged results:<br>
<br>
Setup 1: 492.8 dam<br>
Setup 2: 484.6 dam<br>
<br>
My class specific advantage allows me to do 8 more damage per perf for the price of another 1.5 seconds of delay along with loss of the ability apply 2 poisons at the same time.   <br>
<br>
The point:  Using a 2h to perf is not what everyone thinks it is, and it makes me mad when even the dev's believe it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umelanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>melanu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/5/02 6:33:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3897.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SB's Advantage is being able to crit with 2h weapons?  </span><hr size=1> Hey,<br>
