(AKA lil blue guy)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucyranoofmidgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyrano of Midgard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 8:33:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3897.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SB's Advantage is being able to crit with 2h weapons?  </span><hr size=1> 2h weapons are used in the BGs and on sitting targets. Since I don't think anyone at Mythic has taken a SB past tenth lvl (Sanya) I don't think they understand that. The brain surgeon QA guy quoted earlier sure has no clue. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucyranoofmidgard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyrano of Midgard</A> at: 8/6/02 11:39:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubrandynaquilius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brandyn Aquilius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 10:05:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3897.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SB's Advantage is being able to crit with 2h weapons?  </span><hr size=1> The reason 2H is seen as a bonus to the SB class is that they used to be used to oneshot players for large amounts of damage.  The Critblade spec often yielded damage in excess of 900 points.  Back before epic armor, when we could still remain stealthed after a oneshot, this DID give shadowblades an advantage.  They could oneshot a much higher percentage of their targets, making it more likely that they could kill quite a few people and never get discovered.  Infs one-shotted far less often, most capping damage at around 650 to 700 points.  I'm not sure where NSs capped at, but I'd think it was somewhere around the Infs numbers.<br>
<br>
The primary advantage of the 2H was that you could chain kill people and not really have to worry too much about getting discovered and killed.  With the removal of one-shot stealth, it doesn't really matter much if you do 900 or 600 points of damage (or more realistically 300 or 400 with epic).  Either way you are going to unstealth.  The only advantage I see of a 2H now is that it MIGHT allow you to one-shot someone who might otherwise be able to avoid a second attack (i.e. insta mez, insta stun, insta heal, etc.).<br>
<br>
The 2H weapon thing is kinda cool, but it probably shouldn't be called a real advantage anymore.  There is however, the 15% damage bonus to two handed weapons to consider.  /shrug <p>-Aurra Sing-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uarxantael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arxantael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/6/02 11:37:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3897.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: SB's Advantage is being able to crit with 2h weapons?  </span><hr size=1> 2 Handers are definately a thing of the Past and Battlegrounds.  Has anyone tried out a crit blade on Pendragon?  I'm going to to a crit blade or Zerk there, haven't decided yet which one I want to try. <p>Pitz
