<br>
Total PA damage is base weapon damage + PA bonus damage.  PA bonus damage is not dps based, so all things being equal the bonus damage on the 5.5 and the 4.1 will be the same.  However, the base damage is dps based so a 5.5 spd weap will hit for much more base damage (and thus more total PA damage) than a 4.1 spd weap.     <br>
<br>
Lets do the math:<br>
<br>
5.5/4.1 = 1.34 - the 5.5 is 34% slower, so that if effective DPS, qual, etc. of weapons is the same, the 5.5 will hit for 34% more per swing.  <br>
<br>
If the 5.5 hit for only 8pts more, then 8pts = 34% of your total base damage with the 4.1 spd weapon.  This means that your total base damage with the 4.1 spd weapon was only 23.53 points (1/.34 = 2.94117  and 2.94117 X 8 pts = 23.53 pts).  A base damage of only 23.53 is not really a fair example because I'm sure a lvl 50 hits for a much, much higher base damage then that.  <br>
<br>
Here is a more realistic example:  if a 4.1 spd weapon would have hit for 132 base damage then moving to a 5.5 spd will add an additional 45 points of damage  (177).   Since each lvl of CS adds only +9 to PA CAP (which transilates into a mere 4.5 pts on average) using a 5.5 spd weapon is like having an additional 10 levels of Crit Strike with a 4.1 spd weapon.  <br>
<br>
This means alot.  The slowest Albion thruster I can use is 3.7 spd gladius.  I would have hit for 119 base dmg.  177 damage with a 5.5 2-H is like a 13 CS lvl advantage over me.  Not to mention, I didn't even account for the additional damage bonus 2-H weaps have.  <br>
<br>
A 2-H means you'll one-shot more than a 1-H weap user w/ equal CS spec.  Even with the one-shot-stealth nerf, this is still important.  It  means your more likely to avoid insta mez, heal, stun, etc.  <br>
<br>
Alternatively, the 2-H advantage lets you spec 10 or more levels lower in CS then an Inf/NS, and still have the same PA damage.  You can put all the extra spec points into LA which is much, much better then DW/CD.  <br>
<br>
Just hotkey your 1-H weapons and switch after PA.  Even though an Inf or NS has the chance to hit with off hand on PA and apply 2 poisons, there is also a chance he may have to wait 2-3 combat rounds before off hand swings.  The fact that the LA user will always swing w/ both weapons every round makes up for using a single 2-H weapon in the first combat round.  <br>
<br>
