<br>
Prior to evade fixes and dodger, frontloaded 2h damage was always superiour to 1 handed / dual for a number of reasons, some of which include<br>
<br>
#1  1h users attack faster for less damage.  When the target is out of view / range they gain more delay between attacks (or lose rounds of attack).  A good critblade could garrot, which does snare (and the snare will stick because there is no second hit), kite a few steps out of range, and garrot again - repeat, which effectivly makes the dual wield user's higher speed dual weapons much less effective.  Prior to the /stick fix, there was really no way at all to keep up with a joust fighter other than doing the same thing they are doing, which doesnt work with dual wield.<br>
<br>
#2.  faster and slower weapons of equal dps (excluding the 2h damage bonus) may do the same damage over time, but the 2h will always do it faster because the 1h requires a second hit.  3 round fights favor 2h weapons when the person's chance to avoid the attack is virtually nothing.<br>
<br>
